reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 27, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Use it for movies on deployment and music for djing. Small and portable. It does the job quick and without any issues so far. It connects right to my phone and plays content but for some reason won’t connect to my tv via hdmi. I’m not sure if it is a tv issue or the flash drive issue. Still have 5 stars because I’m still happy with product.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 10, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This helped me a lot with saving storage as a content creator! Its super easy to use and 1tb has a lot of storage for me. I even bought another one. It's fast too. I reccomded this!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 23, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good product, good price.
reviews.reviewText: Works perfectly, fast copying to retrieving and from drive, small and compact.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 9, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Easy, light, reliable
reviews.reviewText: I have had a 2tb version of this for 3 years, for my 50,000 photographs. I keep that one attched at all times, and run LightRoom directly from it as well.I bought this smaller 1tb to use for Time Machine backups. It is even smaller in physical size than the 2tb. Very handy, slick, and perfect for travel too.The only negative: In the pictures it is shown attached to a MacBook using a USB-C to USB-C cable, but the cable in the box is USB C to A. So I haver to use an adapter on it. Bummer! The 2tb came with a C to C cable.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 1, 2023
reviews.reviewText: It's an external ssd. It's portable. Transfer speeds depends on your device. It's quick when your device is quick. If not, then it's not. Smaller than i was expecting. About as small as my T5 or T7 Touch. But it's small enough that it can fit in your pocket and you'll forget it's there. It's plasticky so don't be dropping it left and right. But it's light. And it works. What more do you need? I don't know if it's encryption-capable. Haven't tried nor will i ever. It's not going to be used for any stolen classified information. Those i keep in my spare bathroom.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 8, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Nice fast, small external drive
reviews.reviewText: Not sure how to review this as a purchase from Amazon. I did order it but it was damaged so I had to send it back. I did buy the exact drive somewhere else so this should work. Because It's an SSD drive, it is very fast, small and light. No external power source needed. It has a USB-C interface and connects directly to my laptop. I'm using it with a Mac so a simple reinitialize was necessary. It has a small rubber tab to add a clip or lanyard if you want to carry it with (or to manage the cable as I did). Since there are no moving parts, it is super quiet, like no sound what-so-ever. That fact should also help with the longevity of this drive.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 1, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Tons of space in small form factor
reviews.reviewText: I am just starting to use this for a few days now but so far it's working very well.I re-formatted the drive, loaded VeraCrypt and I'm off. I prefer working with an encryption file format that I already know rather than the encryption software that comes pre-loaded.I've been so impressed that I bought a second one!A nice thing is that it's plug and play with my Samsung Note 20 (no encryption for that but I can move photos and videos, or whatever right to the drive and clear up the phone's storage). This is my plan for the second drive. I wish it were possible to save right to the drive as I took pictures, as this might be nice on occasion (e.g., during a special event) but that doesn't appear to be an option. Still, it's a nice way to keep the phone storage free by downloading every so often on the road.I appreciate the small size and big storage (I got the 2 Terabyte versions).Look forward to seeing how they perform over time. It makes me feel good that SanDisk is owned by Western Digital, as I've relied on their drives for years and never had any problems.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 8, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Best product out there
reviews.reviewText: This, to me, is by far the best external or portable SSD out there as of now. I have tried many others and they either break down on me in a short period or they are just flimsy and made of cheap materials. This product is sturdy and robust and I have dropped it many times and it keeps ticking. I am glad that SanDisk decided to make a line of external SS drives that are catered to rough and "clumsy people" like myself since I am always on the go and this item gives me the confidence that I would not lose anything data or that it would just spontaneously break down on me like some others I have had. The built is SOLD and it doesn't feel delicate like the other external SSDs I have had. So far, I have purchased 5 of these SSDs from SanDisk (beginning 6 years ago) - and so far so good!
Portátil, leve e bastante rápido. Muito bom. Funciona muito bem.
Very small you can easily slip it in your pocket. Usb c port and very fast. The price is very cheap and durable product
